Influential billionaire businessman Bundotich Zedekiah Kiprop, known as Buzeki, is likely to run for Uasin Gishu governor, upsetting the political apple cart. Buzeki&rsquo;s entry will dramatically change the political landscape and upset his rivals&rsquo; strategies.He has invested heavily in the county, the home county of Deputy President William Ruto. He has investments nationwide.Buzeki, a short form of his name, announced at the weekend that he had been approached by residents to stand for the county top job against Governor Jackson Mandago. &ldquo;As a resident of this county, I have a calling to come back and help build it. The time has come for us to give back to the community and share the knowledge we have to benefit all of us,&rdquo; Buzeki said. He spoke at Kapseret in Eldoret during a church function. He was accompanied by area MP Oscar Sudi, Nandi Hills MP Alfred Keter, Uasin Gishu Deputy Governor Daniel Chemno and Mombasa-based businessman David Langat. The Uasin Gishu governor race had been seen as a two horse race between Mandago and Edward Serem, chief Health officer in Nandi county. &ldquo;We are investors in this county and other parts of the country. The work we have done is evident,&rdquo; Buzeki said.